>
>CV joints are cheap replacing em is a PITA, I always work under "if in
>doubt throw it out" when it comes to CV joints

I concur. Minor pitting means you are on the road to short term failure. It 
might just last another 3, 5 or 7 thousand miles. Then again, it may only 
last a few weeks. The only way to eliminate risk is with a new joint, or a 
used joint that will pass inspection.

